Good combination, but like other reviewers, I changed the way I put the ingredients together. I put salt and pepper on the pork loin and seared it in olive oil, then put it into the oven to roast. Then I added the garlic and shallots to the pan and browned them. I sliced 2 small pears into the pan with the garlic and onions, and browned them a little before adding thyme springs, the chicken stock (1/2 cup) and pear nectar (1/2 cup) mixed with approx 1 T flour. I let everything simmer about 5 minutes and thicken while the pork finished cooking, and removed the thyme sprigs just before serving. Served with sauteed brussel sprouts and butternut squash gratin--delicious!

