Rating: 3
This was great! And fairly quick & easy too. The one thing I was concerned about was the direction to cook until a thermometer read 145 -- pork is supposed to reach 160, so I kept it in the oven till the thermometer hit 155 and let carryover heat do the last 5... I saw a couple reviews that the pork had come out bland, so I brined mine and it was fantastic. I boiled a cup of water and stirred in: 1/4 cup of kosher salt, 1/4 cup of brown sugar, 1 minced garlic clove, some thyme and some peppercorns. I added a cup of ice to cool it down and put it in a ziplock with the tenderloin. The pear nectar I bought was more than 3/4 cup so I added the extra, then enough water to cover up the tenderloin, and let it sit for 8 or 9 hours. After that I followed the recipe just as written (except the 10 extra degrees). It came out SO tender, and the sauce was delish. I served it over brown rice. If I make it again I'll probably try doing it all in a roasting pan, and maybe apples instead of pears, like some reviewers suggested. But I was very happy just as it was!

