Rating: 4
This recipe gets 4 forks but only with some relatively major tweaks. First some one forgot seasoning, no salt & pepper, REALLY? Here was my plan. Make the oil, garlic, thyme mixture in a LARGE bowl, heavily season with S&P. Toss in pork & shallots as u heat up an large oven proof skillet. Remove pork & shallots into hot pan, leaving remaining marinade in bowl, toss in & coat pears. Brown pork on all sides about 1.5-2 min per side. Toss in pears and place in hot oven. This way everything roasts together and get goo flavor. Roast until pork is at 145. Place pork, shallots & pears out of pan & place pan back on burner. I don't like gravy (but you can make it as written) so I just deglazed the pan with the pear nectar and broth. Taste sauce & season. It's a GREAT winter dinner. Served with Kale with butternut squash & cranberries.

